Here is an example of how I can help you paraphrase the given passage: 

Original:
In order to reach my goal, I have created a six-month plan in which I will put all my efforts and give it my best shot. In case there appears any unforeseen challenge, by facing it with determination and courage, I shall overcome the obstacle without losing any enthusiasm.

Paraphrased: 
To achieve my objective, I've devised a half-year strategy that involves putting forth maximum effort and dedication. Should unexpected setbacks present themselves, confronting them decisively and bravely enables me to surmount such difficulties without dampening my motivation.
